Choose a reputable free VPN service (e.g., ProtonVPN free tier, Windscribe free) and sign up.

Download and install the VPN client.

Connect to a VPN server.

Screenshot: Take a screenshot of the VPN client interface showing a "Connected" status and the chosen server location.

Check that your IP address has changed (use a website like whatismyipaddress.com).

Screenshot: Capture the website showing the new, virtual IP address and location.

Browse a website to confirm traffic is encrypted. (This step is for conceptual understanding; the actual encryption is confirmed through research and the VPN's status).

Research VPN encryption and privacy features.
